                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17200303-18-off98 t17200303-18-crimeloc101"></join>) about 7 a Clock that Night; that he made his Doors and Shutters fast; that when he came back there was a Stone in his Lock, so that he could not get his Key in; that he went out and got a Porter with a Light, and took the Stone out of the Lock, and when he went in found a Person in his Chambers, who immediately jumpt out at the Window; that the Glass was broke and the Window shutter cut, and the Goods mentioned in the Indictment gone. 
