            , the Constable, deposed that when he took him, (which was on the other side of the Water in Bed about Noon) he said he was a dead Man, owned he had been Transported, but neither consefs'd nor deny'd this Fact and that when he was carried before the Justice, he said he should never come back again. The Prisoner deny'd the Fact on his Tryal, and said that Downing had been condemn'd for his Life, and been pardon'd by King George and that he Swore against him now to save his own Life. The Jury found him <rs id="t17200303-18-verdict102" type="verdictDescription">
